definitions.definition: (of a liquid) To traverse (i.e. be conveyed by capillary action) through a wick or other porous material, as water through a sponge. Usually followed by through.
definitions.example: The moisture slowly wicked through the wood.

definitions.definition: To strike (a stone) obliquely; to strike (a stationary stone) just enough that the played stone changes direction.
